<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKENOT-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CELESTAND GETS A SHOT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX _ The Los Angeles Lakers activated a guard from the
injured list Monday, but it wasn't Kobe Bryant. That move might
happen by the end of the week.
</P>
<P>
   In the meantime, they'll see what John Celestand can do. The
6-foot-3 rookie joined the active roster to replace second-year
guard Tyronn Lue, who went to the injured list with a sore right
knee.
</P>
<P>
   Celestand, a second-round pick in June, came to training camp as
a long shot but played so well in the exhibition season that the
Lakers stashed him on the injured list. Coach Phil Jackson said he
wouldn't hesitate to play Celestand immediately. And he will have
to _ Lue was averaging 18.3 minutes per game, and Bryant isn't due
back for at least a few more days.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's impressive,'' Jackson said of Celestand. ``He grew on me
as a player that plays some pretty good defense and starting
picking up the offensive things.''
</P>
<P>
   Lue said he's been bothered by tendinitis in his right knee for
three weeks but had been playing through the pain until it became
unbearable.
</P>
<P>
   ``It got worse and worse. The last four games it got worse,''
said Lue, who was averaging 6.0 points and 2.1 assists. ``When I'm
sliding or trying to make a move, that's when it hurts the worst. .
. . It's hard when I bend to shoot. My teammates were saying they
can tell I'm dragging.''
</P>
<P>
   Lue will work with trainer Gary Vitti while he sits the
NBA-minimum five games, and the injury isn't expected to be a
long-term problem.
</P>
<P>
   __ Dribbles: Rookie swingman Devean George also was out of
action Monday after coming down with the flu. . . .
</P>
<P>
   Jackson said the Lakers are not interested in signing veteran
forward Armen Gilliam, waived Monday by the Orlando Magic.
</P>
<P>
   ``If he played the defense and rebounded like he plays offense
and posts up, I'd definitely be interested in Armen Gilliam,''
Jackson said. ``He's kind of converse to what we need. We need a
plugger in the lane and a we need a guy to rebound. At this point
he's a very interesting player with a lot of experience, but our
posts are pretty well covered by Shaquille (O'Neal).''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
