<HEADLINE>
WINNING AT HOME KEY TO A PLAYOFF BERTH, COWBOYS COACH SAYS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CLARENCE E. HILL JR. 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ Much has been made about the Dallas Cowboys'
problems on the road, especially against nondivision teams.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys, 0-4 on the road this season, are 0-9 against
non-division opponents on the road since 1997.
</P>
<P>
   The flip side is that the Cowboys have been stellar at home,
which Cowboys coach Chan Gailey said could be the key to their
playoff hopes in the parity-filled NFL in 1999.
</P>
<P>
   Sunday's victory against the Green Bay Packers was the Cowboys'
12th consecutive in the regular season at Texas Stadium. They are
4-0 at home in 1999.
</P>
<P>
   Gailey said it's no coincidence.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think our guys do take a little extra pride playing at
home,'' Gailey said. ``Home games are important; you have to take
care of your home schedule. It's one of the factors in getting into
the playoffs.''
</P>
<P>
   Gailey said the Texas Stadium crowd made a big difference
against the Packers and could be a big factor as the season goes
on.
</P>
<P>
   ``I thought the crowd was into it,'' Gailey said. ``If we can
keep this going, they will make a big difference down the stretch.
We've got some important games coming up at home.''
</P>
<P>
   After traveling to Arizona to face the Cardinals this weekend,
four of the Cowboys' final six games are at home.
</P>
<P>
   Gailey is not overlooking the Cowboys road troubles, saying they
need to win a couple on the road too. CUNNINGHAM SAVES HIS JOB
</P>
<P>
   A week after saying Richie Cunningham is our kicker, Chan Gailey
admitted that there had been thoughts of replacing the struggling
kicker.
</P>
<P>
   The thoughts got stronger in the first quarter against the
Packers when Cunningham missed a 22-yard field-goal attempt that
dropped him to 6-for-14 for the season.
</P>
<P>
   But Cunningham bounced back with makes of 44 and 47 yards. None
were bigger than the former, which came as time expired in the
first half after the kicking team had to be rushed on the field
with no timeouts.
</P>
<P>
   Gailey said the situation was probably best for Cunningham, as
he didn't have time to think. Gailey also praised the entire
kicking unit, namely snapper Dale Hellestrae, holder Eric Bjornson
and members of the offensive line for keeping up with the clock.
</P>
<P>
   The big winner was Cunningham, who was greeted with a huge hug
by offensive tackle Erik Williams following the kick.
</P>
<P>
   Gailey said there's no doubt that Cunningham and the whole team
are relieved and that everybody wants him to do well. But he said
the key now is becoming more consistent and warned against people
getting too carried away with patting him on the back. COWBOYS WORK
OUT DBs
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys worked out two players Monday and plan on looking at
former Cowboy Wendell Davis on Tuesday in an attempt to shore up
their injury-depleted secondary.
</P>
<P>
   With cornerback Kevin Mathis doubtful and Deion Sanders
questionable for the Cardinals game with strained hamstrings, the
Cowboys are looking to make a roster move. It could come as soon as
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   The players who worked out Monday were three-year veterans
Donnie Brady and Vashone Adams. Davis is looking to get back into
the league after being released by the Cowboys in the offseason. He
hasn't played since 1997, as he missed the entire 1998 season with
a knee injury. INJURY REPORT Official injury report for Cardinals
game
</P>
<P>
   _ WR Michael Irvin (spinal cord injury) _ out
</P>
<P>
   _ OL Larry Allen (sprained knee) _ out
</P>
<P>
   _ FS Kenny Wheaton (torn meniscus right knee) _ out
</P>
<P>
   _ FS Izell Reese (strained neck) _ out
</P>
<P>
   _ WR Wane McGarity (separated shoulder) _ doubtful, will try to
practice this week
</P>
<P>
   _ QB Troy Aikman (concussion) _ doubtful
</P>
<P>
   _ CB Kevin Mathis (strained left hamstring) _ doubtful
</P>
<P>
   _ CB Deion Sanders (strained right hamstring, groin) _
questionable
</P>
<P>
   _ RB Emmitt Smith (fractured right hand) _ questionable
</P>
<P>
   _ WR Alvin Harper (strained left quadricep) _ probable
</P>
<P>
   _ C Dale Hellestrae (broken left middle finger_ probable
</P>
<P>
   _ RB Robert Chancey (sprained ankle) _ probable
</P>
<P>
   _ FS George Teague (shoulder contusion) _ probable nn
</P>
