<P>
   &UR; BUSINESS DAY _ (Moved in ``f'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ATM-FEES (Santa Monica, Calif.) _ This suburb of Los Angeles
last month passed the nation's first local ordinance banning banks
from charging non-customers for using their ATMs, and Bank of
America retaliated by denying non-customers use of its machines.
San Francisco voters approved a similar measure earlier this month,
and now, legislators in other cities and states are said to be
looking at similar ordinances. New York City Council speaker Peter
Vallone said he plans to propose such a law, and the Los Angeles
City Council has instructed the city attorney to study the city's
authority to enact such a ban. By Andrew Pollack.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Graphic has been sent to NYT graphics clients.)
</P>
<P>
   LOBBY (Washington) _ When lobbying first became a serious
profession a few decades ago, the ground rules were pretty basic.
About two dozen members of Congress decreed the way most issues
were decided, and an effective lobbyist had to cultivate a personal
relationship with at least one of them to have any real influence.
But now lobbying has turned into a well-ordered global business,
with the influence game taking on a decidedly corporate look. By
Neil A. Lewis.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photo has been sent to NYT graphics clients.)
</P>
<P>
   DRUG-MARKETPLACE _ Following developments in the takeover
struggle being waged by Pfizer, Warner Lambert and American Home
Products.
</P>
<P>
   WEB-STARS-AD-COLUMN (Undated) _ Cyberspace is becoming filled
with stars, as more and more dot-com marketers build their ads
around celebrities. By Stuart Elliott.
</P>
<P>
   (The column is scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ENTERTAINMENT &LR;   &UR; (Moved in ``e'' category) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FORSYTH-PHANTOM (Undated) _ Frederick Forsyth talks about his
new book, ``The Phantom of Manhattan.'' By Alan Cowell.
</P>
<P>
   IRAN-FILM (Undated) _ Arts Abroad: The first western movie to be
made in Iran since the revolution and it's about Islam. By John F.
Burns.
</P>
<P>
   SLEEPING-BOOK-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``Sleeping with
Extra-Terrestrials,'' by Wendy Kaminer (Pantheon). Reviewed by
Michiko Kakutani.
</P>
