<P>
   MONEYTALK _ Financial planning books are on the rise for several
reasons. One is that more and more Americans have investments. One
recent study showed that 52 percent of American households own
stocks or stock mutual funds. Another reason is that we feel more
responsible for building our own financial future and less
confident we can do it. In another study, 45 percent of men and 53
percent of women said they worry about having enough money for the
future. But most of them are sound, and some of them are very good.
(Ezell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
