<HEADER>
A1305 &Cx1f; ttd-z
r l BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRO     11-16 0692
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LETTING A GUY BE A GUY, SORT OF
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   At the San Francisco Zoo, sensitive souls recently performed a
vasectomy on  &UR; Roy &LR; , a 5-month-old blackbuck antelope whom they
didn't want to become a father.
</P>
<P>
   The reason they didn't castrate the animal, which would have
been an easier procedure: Male blackbucks are born light brown, &LR; 
but eventually become black; castration would prevent that
darkening. Although zoo officials felt strongly about limiting his
reproductive activities, ``we still want him to look like a male,''
said zoo representative  &UR; Nancy Chan &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   Because of Roy's young age, he is not fully integrated into the
blackbuck community, but when he reaches sexual maturity at 2 or
so, ``he will still be interested in females,'' veterinarian  &UR; John &LR; 
 &UR; Ochsenreiter  &LR; told Personals. Roy's possible rival for female
attentions is a rather aged male blackbuck _ also, as they say,
shooting blanks _ in residence. Although neither can become a
father, the dueling suitors will have to work out the details of
romance between among &LR;  themselves.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; AL AND BILL &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Joe Klein  &LR; and  &UR; Jane Mayer  &LR; say in the latest New Yorker that
 &UR; Al &LR;   &UR; Gore &LR; 's biggest campaign aim is to dissociate himself from the
Clinton administration, and more personally, from  &UR; Bill &LR; 
 &UR; Clinton &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   Gore told the writers, ``Bill Clinton sees a car going down the
street and he says, `What are the political implications of that
car?' I see a car going down the street and I think, `How can we
replace the internal-combustion engine of that car?' ''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; JOANIE OF ARC &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Winston Smith  &LR; says he's not going to go see ``The
Messenger, &LR; '' because he hears that its star,  &UR; Milla Jovovich &LR; ,
``really makes an ash of herself.''
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, UC Press is reissuing  &UR; Marina Warner &LR; 's 1981 book,
``Joan of Arc: The Image of Female Heroism.'' One of Warner's minor
speculations is that the French heroine may have been anorexic.
``Several witnesses commented during her vindication how even after
battle she only soaked some bread in a little wine.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; HAVING IT BOTH WAYS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   The world's third-largest tobacco company has bought the rights
to lung-cancer vaccines being developed in America, giving the
company the ability to profit from both fostering the disease and
treating it.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Howard Pearlstein &LR;  forwards a report from the British medical
journal Lancet, which says that Japan Tobacco has purchased the
rights to the vaccines, which are still in development, from Cell
Genesys and Corixa. ``Japan Tobacco seems to be pursuing a strategy
of creating a high level of synergy between its product
divisions,'' says Lancet. ``... As Japan Tobacco's investment in
its pharmaceutical division reaps benefits in new products,
clinicians may be faced with some troubling ethical issues.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ In a story about supermodels-turned-actors, Entertainment
Weekly assesses  &UR; Christie Brinkley &LR; 's performance last season in
``Mad About You.'' ``Bottom line: The script called for her to be
tall, blond and have nice teeth _ and she pulled it off
beautifully.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Following last week's revelation that &UR; Newt Gingrich &LR;  had given
his girlfriend,  &UR; Callista Bisek &LR; , a $1,300 set of Calloway golf
clubs,  &UR; Neil Travis  &LR; of the New York Post comments that he detects
``the hand of D.C.'s Mr. Fix-It,  &UR; Vernon Jordan &LR; , here.'' Jordan is
on the board of Calloway and gets deals on the clubs for
Washingtonians perceived to be influential.
</P>
<P>
   _ Product placement: The Berkeley Bark sends proud word that its
``Dog Is My Co-Pilot'' bumper sticker was seen on a refrigerator on
the ``Dharma &AMP; Greg'' show last week.
</P>
<P>
   _ Fox News Channel editors wouldn't let abortion opponent  &UR; Matt &LR; 
 &UR; Drudge &LR;  show a National Enquirer picture of a 21-week-old fetus on
his show on Saturday, so Drudge walked off before airtime.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   `` `Sir Sting' doesn't have much of a ring to it. It's going to
have to be Lord Sting or nothing.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Sting, in Rolling Stone, on the possibility of knighthood.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
