<P>
   &UR; COMMENTARY (k) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   LANGUAGE-COLUMN (Undated) -- We are not bemused. By Jan Freeman.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS (e) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MEDIA-ATLANTIC (Boston) _ The two men who recently took over the
helm of The Atlantic Monthly, Boston's 142-year-old literary
landmark that was once home to Emerson and Thoreau, could not seem
more different. By Mark Jurkowitz. 1870 words.
</P>
<P>
   AUTHOR-MCFEELY (Cambridge, Mass.) _ Historian Bill McFeely,
after testifying as an expert witness for an inmate on death row,
