   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   EGYPT-CRASH _ CAIRO _ The reaction and other developments from
Egypt to the latest news about the pilot in the crash of EgyptAir
Flight 990. Developing. (Kaplow, Cox News Service
</P>
<P>
   CLINT0N-OSCE _ ISTANBUL _ With fighting raging between Russian
troops and Chechen rebels several hundred miles from here,
President Clinton will lead his counterparts from the 54-nation
Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe, OSCE, in their
annual summit. Chechnya appears certain to dominate the forum _ the
civil analog to the NATO military alliance. We set up the summit.
(Deans, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   OSCE-JOHNSON _ VIENNA _ An interview, if possible, with U.S.
Ambassador to the Vienna-based OSCE, David Johnson, a career
diplomat and young father of three from Columbus, Ga. Developing.
(Deans, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   CZECH-WALL _ PRAGUE, Czech Republic _ With a badge and a gun and
a loyal following, Maj. Jan Zeman is back on duty 10 years after
the end of communist rule, in pursuit of lawbreakers and
subversives who threaten the social order. The fictional Maj. Zeman
was the former Czechoslovakia's favorite television police
detective during communist times. A decision by Czech Television to
re-broadcast the 1970s serial has raised a fierce debate in the
Czech Republic over whether the show is propaganda or entertainment
or history. It comes at a sensitive time when the present-day
Communist Party is enjoying a surge in support amid the country's
economic malaise. (Holmes, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   (Eds: The anniversary of the Czech ``Velvet Revolution'' is
Wed., Nov. 17. Re-sending this story for those papers who haven't
used it previously.) WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   SCHOOLS-POLL _ WASHINGTON _ Would you send your child to a good
school near your home or to a better school that is pretty
difficult to get to? In a national poll released by Public Agenda,
the nonpartisan, nonprofit research group, 40 percent chose the
closest school and 54 percent chose the better school. The
pollsters also discovered that most parents aren't interested in
and admit knowing ``little'' or ``nothing'' about two often-touted
reforms _ school vouchers and public charter schools. (Mollison,
Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   AFFIRMATIVE-REACTION _ WASHINGTON _ Rep. Alcee Hastings of
Florida and other black Democratic House members join
representatives of the NACCP and the National Urban League at a
news conference Friday to discuss ``Florida Gov. Jeb Bush's
proposal to end affirmative action in Florida.'' (Schultz, Cox News
Service)
</P>
<P>
   Y2K-MOVIE _ WASHINGTON _ ``Y2K: The Movie'' is an
``irresponsible'' spark that could
</P>
<P>
   light a panic among many Americans. But it also could do some
good if it leads
</P>
<P>
   people to take sensible precautions for Jan. 1 computer
glitches. That was the
</P>
<P>
   split verdict among a dozen government and industry officials
who gathered with
</P>
<P>
   a reporter this week to watch a preview copy of the NBC
suspense-thriller, which
</P>
<P>
   airs at 9 p.m. EST Sunday. (Geewax, Cox News Service) WITH
PHOTOS.
</P>
