   POLITICS
</P>
<P>
   BUSH _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Most presidential candidates have been
burning up the talk show circuit for months. Front-running George
W. Bush finally makes his debut this week, with an appearance on
20/20 Wednesday, and on Sunday's Week in Review. (Herman, Austin
American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   BRADLEY-FUND _ ATLANTA _ Democratic presidential candidate Bill
Bradley will be
</P>
<P>
   in Atlanta today for a fund-raiser at the home of Anne Cox
Chambers, a media magnate and former Gore supporter who parted ways
with the VP over cable regulation. He will also meet with students
and faculty at Morehouse Medical School. Later Bradley will meet
with members of the Jewish community, many of whom are in town for
the United Jewish Communities' General Assembly. (Foskett, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BRADLEY-ADS _ WASHINGTON _ Democrat Bill Bradley debuts his
first television advertisements of the campaign Tuesday. The ads,
produced by a Madison Avenue ad team, will run in Iowa and New
Hampshire beginning Wednesday. As merits. (Foskett, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
