<HEADLINE>
KANSAS CITY STAR BUDGET 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Kansas City Star plans to move the following stories for use
by clients of the NYTimes News Service for AMs and PMs of
Wednesday, Nov. 17. If you have any questions, please call The
Star's News Desk at (816) 234-4720.
</P>
<P>
   JOBS: Amid all the hand-wringing in Kansas City about the
probable and possible job losses at Sprint and Hoechst, a new
Brookings Institution report shows Kansas City enjoyed some of the
best job growth in the country at the beginning of the current
economic expansion, from 1993-96. The metro area ranked 9th among
the 30 most-populated metros. Also, data from the U.S. Bureau of
Labor Statistics shows this decade is Kansas City's best job-growth
performance in at least three decades. Jeffrey Spivak and Brad
Cooper. Graphic. 30.
</P>
