acquired by MCI WorldCom Inc. with the Federal Communications
Commission. By Ted Sickinger Visuals.
</P>
<P>
   HEASTER _ Jerry Heaster column.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS BUDGET OFFERS:
</P>
<P>
   HOLMGREN. It's easy to see the imprint Mike Holmgren has left on
the Seattle Seahawks in just nine games as coach and general
manager. His team is 7-2 and looks like the division's toughest
team, his quarterback looks like a Pro Bowler and his old team
looks like they still need him. As they say, it's good to be the
king. Jonathan Rand. 25-30. With SIDEBAR on quarterback Jon Kitna.
</P>
<P>
   ROYALS. Update on the Royals' bizarre ownership situation.
Steven Rock.
</P>
<P>
   CHIEFS. How can the Chiefs operate a pro offense if they keep
getting scared when something goes wrong? Jimmy Raye admitted he
got conservative after Elvis Grbac fumbled Sunday against Tampa
Bay. And yet, his team desperately needs to play a more wide-open
game to win. Randy Covitz. 18-20.
</P>
<P>
   POZ. Joe Posnanski column.
</P>
<P>
   KSHOOP. Kansas State at No. 10 Arizona in preseason NIT, 9:30
p.m. start. Blair Kerkhoff. 17. Photos
</P>
