<P>
   &UR; FOCUS (Available by 2 p.m., Fri., Nov. 19) &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CHINA: MUSLIMS: A look at the smoldering resentment among
China's Muslims in the country's far western frontier, a
third-world backwater culturally and physically remote from China's
political center. Mostly members of a Turkic minority called
Uighers, they protest Beijing's grasp on their resources and
autocratic rule in mostly quiet ways. But the radical fringes of
the 8 million Uighurs continue waging a hit-and-run campaign of
violence.
</P>
