   YOUNG-HUNTERS (Chester, N.J.) _ Shooting programs for children
are nothing new; the NRA and private gun clubs have had them for
generations. In recent years, state wildlife agencies around the
country have run special youth hunts for an assortment of game,
including wild pigs, rabbits, ducks and deer. But a recent New
Jersey pheasant shoot was an example of a newer and growing
phenomenon _ of public state-wildlife agencies and the gun lobby
working hand in hand to promote hunting among children. By Andrew
C. Revkin.
