<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-11-16 19:02 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A1694 &Cx1f; ttd-z
r a BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRO     11-16 0769
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MATCH THE DISS WITH THE DISSER AND DISSEE
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``l'' lifestyle file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   Movieline magazine has collected 50 memorable put-downs from the
mouths of stars, 10 of which are the subject of today's pop quiz.
Who said these things about whom?
</P>
<P>
   1) ``I always knew (he) would end up in bed with a little boy.''
</P>
<P>
   2) ``Working with her is like being hit over the head with a
Valentine's card.''
</P>
<P>
   3) ``She demonstrated certifiable proof of insanity.''
</P>
<P>
   4) ``It was a matter of a young actor who was an ex-Marine out
of Brooklyn meeting with a talented director who was out of UCLA
and some fraternity.''
</P>
<P>
   5) He is ``the kind of man who will end up dying in his own
arms.''
</P>
<P>
   6) ``I'd love to work with her again, in something appropriate.
Perhaps `Macbeth.'''
</P>
<P>
   7) ``Working with her is like being bombarded with
watermelons.''
</P>
<P>
   8) ``She's slept with every male star at MGM except Lassie.''
</P>
<P>
   9) She's ``a half-assed chorus girl, a pseudo-intellectual who
thinks she knows politics, thinks she knows everything, wears
clothes from the ladies of the Good Christ Church Bazaar.''
</P>
<P>
   10) He's a ``bloated, over-the-hill, adolescent entertainer _
had nothing to do with excellence, just myth.''
</P>
<P>
   Answers: 1)  &UR; Ava Gardner &LR;  about  &UR; Frank Sinatra &LR; 's marriage to
 &UR; Mia Farrow &LR; ; 2)  &UR; Christopher Plummer  &LR; about working with  &UR; Julie &LR; 
 &UR; Andrews  &LR; on ``The Sound of Music''; 3)  &UR; Roman &LR;   &UR; Polanski  &LR; on  &UR; Faye &LR; 
 &UR; Dunaway &LR; , who starred in ``Chinatown''; 4) &UR; Harvey Keitel &LR;  after
being fired by  &UR; Francis Ford Coppola  &LR; from ``Apocalypse Now''; 5)
 &UR; Mamie Van Doren &LR;  on  &UR; Warren Beatty &LR; ; 6)  &UR; Walter &LR;   &UR; Matthau  &LR; after
working with  &UR; Barbra Streisand &LR;  on ``Hello, Dolly!''; 7)  &UR; Alan
Ladd &LR;  after working with  &UR; Sophia Loren &LR;  in ``Boy on a Dolphin''; 8)
 &UR; Bette Davis &LR;  on  &UR; Joan Crawford &LR; ; 9)  &UR; Martin Rackin &LR; , producer of
``Two Mules for Sister Sara,'' on his star, &UR; Shirley MacLaine &LR; ; 10)
 &UR; Marlon Brando &LR;  on  &UR; Elvis Presley &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   P.S.  &UR; Shane Ham &LR; , a 27-year-old segment producer who recently
quit the ``McLaughlin Group,'' addressed the following resignation
letter, quoted in the Washington Post, to his boss,
 &UR; John McLaughlin &LR; :
</P>
<P>
   ``I would like to thank you for giving me the opportunity to
work on a television show. It's unlikely that any legitimate news
organization would hire someone with no experience, basing the
decision only on a shared passion for dirty jokes about  &UR; President &LR; 
 &UR; Clinton &LR; . ... But you also did so much more than that. You allowed
me to finally test my limits. ... I have stretched my capacity for
abuse and denigration as far as I can go. ... In 10 long months you
and your lovely young wife have given me many years' worth of
anecdotes with which to amaze and amuse my friends.'' McLaughlin is
married to  &UR; Cristina Vidal McLaughlin &LR; , vice president of the
program's production company.
</P>
<P>
   Ham told the Post that he'd heard McLaughlin was difficult, but
``the difference between hearing stories about John McLaughlin and
actually working for him is the difference between watching `Saving
Private Ryan' and landing on D-Day.''
</P>
