<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Wednesday, Nov. 17. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
ROADS (Phoenix) - Urban roads are crowded not because of explosive
population growth but because the people that live in cities drive
more than ever, a national study says. It shows that while the
metro Phoenix population grew by 68 percent from 1982-1997, the
miles driven climbed 131 percent. This left the Phoenix area with
the equivalent of an extra 1.9 million people from a driving
standpoint, according to the analysis by the Surface Transportation
Policy Project. By MARY JO PITZL. Story will move in the ``A''
category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
