Ferdinand Drucker have fallen out of favor with each other.
Drucker, now 90, the author of 31 books, still has his disciples,
but at the bleeding edge of business the old master's lifework is
commonly seen as simplistic, portentous, off the mark, idealistic
and out of date. Not for 20 years have the corporate world's heavy
hitters hung on his every word. By Fred Andrews.
