   GRIDLOCK-STUDY (Los Angeles) -- Los Angeles is ranked as the
most-congested city in the nation for the 17th year in a row,
according to a study by Texas A&AMP;M University released Tuesday. By
Steve Carney. (Will move on the ``n'' California news wire.)
</P>
<P>
   ECONOMY-CALIFORNIA (Los Angeles) -- Southern California's
economic good times are expected to continue over the next two
years, but at a slightly slower rate than the region has enjoyed
since the mid-1990s, according to a new survey released Wednesday
by the Southern California Association of Governments. By Chris
Sieroty. (Will move on the ``f'' financial news wire.)
</P>
<P>
   NETZERO-AIMTV (Los Angeles) -- Newly public internet service
provider NetZero began spending the spoils of its initial public
offering, buying AimTV, a carrier of video advertising on the
Internet. By Jason Z. Cohen. (Will move on the ``f'' financial news
wire.)
</P>
<P>
   STORE-STUDIOS (Los Angeles) -- Disney and Warner are moving
towards cuts in their retail store operations for the first time.
Disney plans to close a store in Atlanta in January; Warner is
considering scaling back its 140 domestic outlets. By Dave McNary.
(Will move on the ``f'' financial news wire.)
</P>
