NY-RADIO-1, 11-16 -- Laura Walker, president and chief executive of
the radio station WNYC, at its Manhattan studios. As the station
celebrates its 75th anniversary, it faces not only continued high
payments for its broadcasting license but a backbreaking 200
percent hike in charges from National Public Radio for syndication
of several programs. (Librado Romero/New York Times Photo)
