<P>
   (NYT23) NEW YORK -- Nov. 16, 1999 -- ADV. FOR SUN., NOV. 21 --
FELDMAN-MUSIC-B&AMP;W, 11-16 -- The composer Morton Feldman at his
Manhattan home in 1967. Feldman was a Brooklyn-born original, for
whom traditional forms and unfolding musical development held
little interest. Rather, he was fascinated by the sounds of
individual notes, the long silences, expansive structures, isolated
chords and spare timbral combinations. (Sam Falk/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT22) TBILISI, Georgia -- Nov. 16, 1999 -- RUSSIA-CAUCASUS-2,
11-16 --Unemployed Georgians playing dominos in a park in Tbilisi.
Georgia wants to avoid helping Russia in the Chechen war, but it is
a poor country and has a long legacy of economic and military
dependence on Russia. (Jacqueline Mia Foster/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT21) KINGS POINT, N.Y. -- Nov. 16, 1999 --
MERCHANT-MARINE-ACADEMY-2, 11-16 -- A cadet walks the grounds at
the United States Merchant Marine Academy in Kings Point, N.Y.
``Acta non verba'' - deeds, not words - is the school's official
motto, but ``make do'' could serve just as well for a place that
has withstood obscurity, the declining prominence of the United
States in global shipping and whacks from federal bean counters.
(Vic Delucia/New York Times Photo)
