Minimalism is an especially good thing when it comes to the pecan
pie. Anne Rosenzweig's version, which she serves at the Lobster
Club in Manhattan, is the perfect example: just a crisp square of
puff pastry topped with a thin layer of molten caramel and toasted
pecans. It's served hot, right out of the oven, with a jaunty
finish - a little cube of vanilla ice cream. (Philip Greenberg/New
York Times Photo)
