POLLUTION-III-BOS, 11-16 -- Gregory Sasse has spent the last 13
years prosecuting polluters on the federal level. Last year, the
EPA awarded Sasse a silver medal for superior service on a task
force that secured the first criminal indictment of a company
violating the law designed to prevent the release of chemicals
hazardous to the ozone. (Tom Herde/Boston Globe Photo)
