<SLUG> BC-NY-BRICK-ATTACK-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WOMAN ON MIDTOWN STREET IS HIT BY MAN WITH A BRICK
</HEADLINE>
   (nk) 
 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ A 27-year-old woman returning from an office errand
Tuesday afternoon was smashed in the head with a brick on a
bustling Midtown sidewalk by a man who then ran off, the police
said.
</P>
<P>
   The woman, Nicole Barrett of Queens, was critically injured and
underwent brain surgery at Bellevue Hospital Center Tuesday night,
hospital officials said. The police said they had no suspects in
the attack, an apparently random act that took place in front of at
least a dozen horrified witnesses.
</P>
<P>
   Ms. Barrett, a temporary worker originally from Texas who was on
the last day of a job assignment on East 42nd Street, was walking
at the corner of East 42nd and Madison Avenue around 3:10 p.m. when
a man in his 30s or 40s walked up behind her, a law enforcement
official said.
</P>
<P>
   Without a word, the man brought a large gray paving stone down
on the back of her head and ran north up Madison Avenue as Ms.
Barrett slumped to the ground, witnesses told the police. The man,
who was black, of medium height and wearing a dark jacket and blue
jeans, turned west on 43rd Street and disappeared into the crowd,
witnesses said.
</P>
<P>
   It was not clear if anyone tried to stop Ms. Barrett's attacker.
A man working in a newsstand a few feet away said he heard a
commotion and ambulances but did not leave his perch to see what
was the matter.
</P>
<P>
   ``We don't look out from here,'' said the man, who would not
give his name. ``The moment we look out, people start taking
things.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
