<SLUG> BC-BBA-ANGELS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ANGELS HOPE TO NAME MANAGER THIS WEEK
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JOE HAAKENSON  
 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Anaheim Angels will hire a manager in the next couple of
days. At least that's what Bill Stoneman hopes to do.
</P>
<P>
   The Angels will hire a scouting director to replace Bob Fontaine
shortly thereafter. At least that's what Stoneman hopes to do.
</P>
<P>
   The Angels will talk to pitcher Chuck Finley about re-signing
with the team. At least that's what Stoneman hopes to do.
</P>
<P>
   It's been a hectic 16 days since Stoneman took over as the
club's general manager Nov. 1. But he knew that coming in.
</P>
<P>
   Stoneman has interviewed seven managerial candidates _ Bob
Boone, Chris Chambliss, Ken Macha, Hal McRae, Joe Maddon, Mike
Scioscia and Joel Skinner _ and he expects to name one of those by
the end of the week.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's my intent,'' Stoneman said. ``(Deciding on a manager)
has been much more time consuming than I thought. It's an in-depth
thing because it's a key decision.''
</P>
<P>
   Stoneman wouldn't say that he's narrowed the list, only that ``I
think I've zeroed in on the direction we want to go. But I'm not
there yet.''
</P>
<P>
   Stoneman's top priority in a manager is ``somebody who is going
to command respect of the players. You win respect, you don't ask
for it. You obtain it by the way you conduct yourself and the
respect you give to other people.''
</P>
<P>
   Stoneman will then move forward on hiring a scouting director,
but in the meantime continues to further the risk of losing Finley.
Finley is meeting with other teams, with the Cleveland Indians
seeming to have the best shot at getting him.
</P>
<P>
   Finley has told friends that he has been disappointed by the
Angels' apparent disinterest. Stoneman says it's just a matter of
getting together and talking.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've had a priority since I first walked through the door to
get together with him and sit down and discuss things,'' Stoneman
said. ``I'm not blindly going to make a decision without first
having an exchange with him. It's something Chuck has known I've
wanted to do for a while, but we haven't been able to do it.
</P>
<P>
   ``I talked to his agent (Tuesday). I hope we can get together
and talk in the new future.''
</P>
<P>
   Stoneman added it's been frustrating trying to get something set
up with Finley.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've tried to make time for everything,'' he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
